Standard and Poor's Corp said it maydowngrade AFG Industries Inc and GenCorp Inc because apartnership affiliated with AFG and Wagner and Brown made a 2.2billion dlr tender offer to acquire GenCorp.    AFG has 185 mln dlrs of BB-plus subordinated debt andGenCorp carries 100 mln dlrs of same-rated subordinated debt.    Financing terms of the proposed acquisition are unknown,including AFG's equity contribution to the partnership. S and Psaid AFG's appetite for substantial acquisitions is aggressive.The tender offer would likely heighten financial risk andincrease leverage for GenCorp, S and P said. Reuter&#3;